cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and reconstruction. It also involves numerical stability and estimation, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories, respectively. The use of matrices in the Radon-Nikodym approach suggests it could also be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the mention of statistical property estimation could indicate a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
